<br>
Say you're using a 20 delay weapon, meaning 2 seconds between swings unhasted.<br>
<br>
Put an FBSS on and it'll reduce delay by ~17% (according to parsed logs, never done it myself)<br>
<br>
So (1-.17) x 2.0 = 1.66s   this is the new, 17% lower delay (edit: actually delay would be 16.6 but you get the point <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Then figure the number of attacks:<br>
<br>
In a 100s period, unhasted would be 50 attacks (100 / 2.0)<br>
<br>
With the new hasted delay:  100 / 1.66 = 60.25 attacks<br>
<br>
To find the percentage increase in attacks (dmg output):<br>
<br>
60.25 / 50 = 1.205<br>
<br>
So the increase in damage output is 20.5%, which of course everyone just rounds up to 21%<br>
<br>
<br>
